        options: ["Diazepam because its long half-life provides sustained effect","Alprazolam because it is the most potent anxiolytic","Lorazepam because it undergoes glucuronidation rather than hepatic CYP metabolism","Chlordiazepoxide because it is the oldest and most studied"],
        correct: 2,
        rationale: "Lorazepam is a LOT drug (Lorazepam, Oxazepam, Temazepam) that undergoes Phase II glucuronidation rather than Phase I CYP oxidation. In hepatic impairment, CYP enzyme function is compromised, leading to dangerous accumulation of CYP-metabolized benzodiazepines (diazepam, alprazolam, chlordiazepoxide). LOT drugs are the safe choice in liver disease."
